1) In "sel_script.py" write valid user creddentials:
        username = "HERE_YOU_SHOULD_WRITE_USERNAME"
        password = "hERE_YOU_SHOULD_WRITE_PASSWORD"



2) Open a terminal in this directory and run the following script:
        
        flask run --host=0.0.0.0



3) You can access the webbrowser on http://192.168.1.5:5000/ from any computer in this office



4) For changing IP - You can run command in a terminal:

        windscibre connect

   for disconnecting you can run command

        windscribe disconnect

   It'll be better if you don't use it, because changing ip slows down the internet connection and linkedin
   might ask for some verifications.